		@G[c3 stills_108.png]@L
		@H Historical Background @L
		Lutetia, modern day Paris, derives its name from the Celtic word "lut" which means swamp. The area had been settled for over 4,500 years. For most of the city's history it had been inhabited by Celtic peoples. Romans annexed the area along with the rest of Gaul after Gaius Julius Caesar waged his campaign of conquests known as the Gallic Wars. The Roman settlement there was only founded in the late 1st century BC during the reign of first citizen Caesar Augustus. @L@L
		
		@G[c3 instructions icon.png]
		@H Instructions @L
		Governor, I have an important assignment for you:  you are to oversee the founding of a Roman colony in Gaul. The city is to be called Lutetia, and the local area is rich in quality timber, iron, and clay. I'm assigning this task to you as the difficulties that will need to be overcome are substantial. 
		Firstly, wild beasts still roam the forests of Gaul and Lutetia is not an exception. Clear out their dens and secure vital farmland in the forest cleanings they inhabit. The locals are numerous and still hostile to Roman presence. Your task will be to seek cooperation but before we can make them conform to Roman ways, they need to be shown strength. @L@L
		Recruit local legions to break their will and show them the futility of resistance. Native peoples also dwell near the potential hidden forest paths, from which still hostile Gallic tribes are sure to attack your city in the future. 
		@L@L
		Designate defensive works to be built in such places and consider strategic matters from where the enemy can approach the city. If you can ensure the security of Lutetia, you are to also assist friendly cities in Roman Gaul, as our grip needs to be solidified. Unfortunately, the long and bloody civil war has left scars on Rome's image as a bringer of stability. @L@L
		Good luck governor, I will be watching your progress closely. @L@L@L

		@H Edicts @L@
