 @G[c3 stills_133.png] 
		@H Message @L
		Governor, sad tidings reached us today. First Citizen Caesar Augustus has passed away. Political turmoil will surely follow. @L@L
		This is a historical note of no gameplay significance. Feel free to skip if you are not interested. @G[cesar.png]@L@L
		@H Historical Background @L
		Augustus never held an official title of "Emperor" or "King". He effectively had unlimited power, in the same way that Gaius Julius Caesar did after he managed to get control over the Senate and Rome. His succession was difficult as he willed titles to his grandsons, but a series of deaths followed the succession until finally in 14 AD Tiberius Julius Caesar Augustus became the first official Roman Emperor. @L@L
		After Caesar's death, Augustus officially adopted his name and, in the eyes of Caesar's assassins and critics, he effectively became not only inheritor of his vast estates, but also of his political mindset and clout. @L@L
		At first, Augustus held a junior role in partnership with Marcus Antonius and Marcus Lepidus in the second triumvirate. This changed later, however, when he asserted his dominance over the Senate. Augustus himself was generally disinterested and bored with command and most matters to do with military or naval warfare. @L@L
		There is no doubt that he was a brilliant statesman and administrator, but most of the command tasks would fall upon Marcus Vipsanius Agrippa, who was his lifelong friend and an extremely talented general. @L@L
		On a final note, unlike how Julius Caesar never created proscription lists or persecuted his enemies, Augustus had no such restraints and proscriptions were used widely. @L@L@L@L

